If you did not apply for the Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) program in May and June, you now have another opportunity to apply. Through this program, each student is eligible to receive a pre-loaded EBT card for $285 to use on groceries. This is only for families who did not apply or receive this benefit in May or June. Because Haynesville schools are part of the Community Eligibility Provision program, ALL Haynesville students are eligible.

Click the link below to apply:
https://pebt.doe.louisiana.gov/PublicApps/SNP/

post_text:
Please help us welcome Mrs. Heather Brooks as our new principal.

Mrs. Brooks taught 12 years in Bossier before becoming an instructional coach in Claiborne Parish. She held the position of instructional coach for 3 years where she spent time working with teachers and principals on curriculum implementation and professional development. Mrs. Brooks states, ‚ÄúI am so excited to begin this journey as principal of Haynesville Elementary. My family loves the Haynesville community and it is truly an honor to join such a wonderful school. Mrs. Brown always said, Haynesville Elementary is a great place to be, and I truly believe that ! My experience in curriculum and leadership as an instructional coach will help me guide Haynesville Elementary to continued growth and academic excellence. Even in these uncertain times, the Haynesville Elementary staff looks forward to helping our students grow and succeed.‚Äù

post_text: Teacher/Staff Appreciation Week starts today. The work our teachers are doing now looks so much different because they aren‚Äôt in the classroom. They went from daily face to face teaching to preparing weeks of packets practically in a matter of a couple of days. They are continuously attempting to meet the needs of their students through phone calls, emails, text messages and zoom meetings to ensure the educational process of all students continues to move forward despite the challenges we are facing on a daily basis. This new way of educating our students is much more stressful & teachers are missing the classrooms and their students. I am so proud of all the staff at Haynesville Elementary and the dedication they have to make Haynesville Elementary a great place to be.

shared_text:
Murphy Arts District
March 30 at 3:10 PM ¬∑

Vincent's Colors virtual workshop added for this Wednesday via facebook live! üé®

Join artist and art educator Gay Bechtelheimer as she reads the book "Vincent's Colors" by Vincent Van Gogh. Afterwards, using crayons, paint, and paper, she will guide children as they create their own composition inspired by the work of Vincent Van Gogh.

Vincent van Gogh is one of the world's most famous artists. Throughout his life, he wrote to his younger brother, Theo, about his colorful, dynamic paintings. This book pairs the artist's paintings with his own words.

Supplies Needed:
‚Ä¢ Crayons
‚Ä¢ Paint
‚Ä¢ 2 pieces of paper (1 piece should be a 6 inch square)

#eldoradoarkansas #virtualworkshop #vincentscolors #homeschool

post_text: Chief Meteorologist Jeff Castle from KSLA-TV channel 12 spoke to our kindergarten students about the weather today. Our students have been learning about the weather in a unit we have been studying in our ELA and Science curriculum. We thoroughly enjoyed his presentation about weather, storm safety, and what it means to be a meteorologist. The students wrote thank you cards and we presented him with a small gift basket to show our token of appreciation for coming to visit. Tune in to channel 12 at 6:00 to see if we get a shout out. Thanks for coming Jeff Castle.
